==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mahwa tree
<hw>Mah"wa tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An East
Indian sapotaceous tree (<spn>Bassia latifolia</spn>, and also
<spn>Bassia butyracea</spn>), whose timber is used for wagon wheels, and
the flowers for food and in preparing an intoxicating drink. It is one
of the butter trees. The oil, known as <xex>mahwa</xex> and
<xex>yallah</xex>, is obtained from the kernels of the fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maia</ent>⟦br⟧
